'''lymphatic system'''

# {{anatomy}} In [[mammal]]s, including [[human]]s, a network of lymphatic vessels and [[lymph node]]s that transport fluid, fats, [[protein]]s, and [[lymphocyte]]s to the [[bloodstream]] as [[lymph]], and remove [[microorganism]]s and other debris from tissues.

